headlines.description: — Franz Wagner scored 22 points and the Orlando Magic held Luka Doncic under 30 points for the first time this season in a 94-87 win over the Dallas Mavericks on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Magic limit Luka Doncic to 24 points, beat Mavericks 94-87

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at Charlotte Hornets

headlines.description: — The Portland Trail Blazers didn't need a buzzer-beater this time.
headlines.shortLinkText: Lillard scores 26, Blazers hand Hornets 6th straight loss

headlines.description: — Nikola Jokic spent the first three quarters watching his teammates do the dirty work.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jokic overcomes foul trouble, Nuggets rally past Pacers

headlines.description: — The best 3-point defense in the NBA was no match for Lauri Markkanen and the Utah Jazz.
headlines.shortLinkText: Markkanen's season-high 32 helps Jazz beat Hawks 125-119

headlines.description: — Jayson Tatum had 31 points and five assists, and the Boston Celtics beat the Detroit Pistons 128-112 on Wednesday night to earn their fourth straight victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: Tatum scores 31, Celtics beat Pistons for 4th straight win

events.name: New York Knicks at Brooklyn Nets

headlines.description: — New coach, same result in a New York basketball rivalry that's become no rivalry at all.
headlines.shortLinkText: Durant, Nets pound Knicks 112-85 after promoting Vaughn

headlines.description: — Fred VanVleet scored 12 of his season-high 32 points in the fourth quarter, O.G. Anunoby matched his season best with 27 points and added 10 rebounds, and the Toronto Raptors beat the Houston Rockets 116-109 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: VanVleet scores season-high 32, Raptors beat Rockets 116-109

events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at Chicago Bulls

headlines.description: — Brandon Ingram scored 18 of his 22 points in the second half, including seven straight late in the fourth quarter, and the New Orleans Pelicans pulled out a 115-111 victory over the Chicago Bulls on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Ingram's 22 points rally Pelicans to 115-111 win over Bulls

headlines.description: — Devin Booker had 32 points and a season-high 10 assists, and Mikal Bridges scored 13 of his season-high 31 points in the first quarter as the Phoenix Suns beat the Minnesota Timberwolves 129-117 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Booker scores 32; Paul-less Suns beat Wolves 129-117

events.name: Milwaukee Bucks at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — Jevon Carter had career highs of 36 points and 12 assists, and the short-handed Milwaukee Bucks beat the Oklahoma City Thunder 136-132 in two overtimes on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Carter scores career-high 36, Bucks beat Thunder in 2 OTs

events.name: Memphis Grizzlies at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — Ja Morant and Desmond Bane had 32 points each and the Memphis Grizzlies beat San Antonio 124-122 in overtime Wednesday night, handing the Spurs their fifth straight loss.
headlines.shortLinkText: Morant, Bane help Grizzlies beat Spurs in overtime, 124-122

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at LA Clippers

headlines.description: — LeBron James scored 30 points before leaving the court with pain in his left leg late in the Los Angeles Lakers' 114-101 loss to the Los Angeles Clippers on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: LeBron hurt late in Clippers' 114-101 win over Lakers

headlines.description: — Domantas Sabonis scored 21 points and the Sacramento Kings overcame another big performance by Donovan Mitchell to beat the Cleveland Cavaliers 127-120 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Sabonis scores 21 points, Kings top Mitchell, Cavs 127-120
